      <div xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e29842">
        <head xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e29842-Hd1e99" type="question-title">De vagatione</head>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e29842-d1e102">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e29842-Qd1e112" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e29842-Rd1e104">Gregorius, in
              <title>Pastorali</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e29842-Qd1e112">Interior est custodia cordis, quae ordinata
              exterius servat membra corporis. Qui ergo statum mentis perdidit, subsequenter foras
              inconstantia motionis fluit; atque exteriore mobilitate indicat, quod nulla interius
              radice constantiae subsistat.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e29842-d1e117">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e29842-Qd1e127" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e29842-Rd1e119">Hieronymus, in
              <title>Epistola</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e29842-Qd1e127">De agmine columbarum crebro accipiter unam
              separat, quam statim invadat et laceret, cujus carnibus et cruore satietur; et
              morbidae oves suum relinquunt gregem, et luporum faucibus devorantur.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e29842-d1e132">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e29842-Qd1e142" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e29842-Rd1e134">Hieronymus, super
            illud <title>Genesis</title>, secundum aliam litteram</ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e29842-Qd1e142">
              <!--<i>-->Egressus Cain a facie Domini habitabat in terra Naid, quod interpretatur
              fluctuatio<!--</i>-->: Quicumque enim a Domino recedit, statim saeculi fluctibus
              quatitur, et moventur pedes ejus.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e29842-d1e151">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e29842-Qd1e161" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e29842-Rd1e153">Seneca, in
              <title>Epistola</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e29842-Qd1e161">Frequens migratio corporis, instabilis animi
              proprium est. Coalescere otio non potes, nisi desinas circumspicere et errare.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e29842-d1e167">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e29842-Qd1e177" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e29842-Rd1e169">Seneca, in
              <title>Epistola</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e29842-Qd1e177">Ut animum possis continere, primo corporis fugam
              siste; deinde remedia continuata plurimum proficiunt.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e29842-d1e182">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e29842-Qd1e192" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e29842-Rd1e184">Seneca, in
              <title>Epistola</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e29842-Qd1e192">Sine discere oculos tuos, sine aures assuescere
              sanioribus verbis: quoties processeris, in ipso transitu aliqua quae renovent
              cupiditates tuas tibi occurrent.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e29842-d1e197">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e29842-Qd1e207" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e29842-Rd1e199">Seneca, in
              <title>Epistola</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e29842-Qd1e207">Primum argumentum compositae vitae existimo,
              posse consistere, et secum morari.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e29842-d1e212">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e29842-Qd1e222" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e29842-Rd1e214">Seneca, in
              <title>Epistola</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e29842-Qd1e222">Non coalescit planta, quae saepe transfertur.
              Nihil tam utile est, quod in transitu prosit.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e29842-d1e227">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e29842-Qd1e237" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e29842-Rd1e229">Seneca, in
              <title>Epistola</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e29842-Qd1e237">Avarior, ambitiosior, luxuriosior, imo vero
              crudelior et inhumanior redeo, quia inter homines fui.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e29842-d1e242">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e29842-Qd1e252" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e29842-Rd1e244">Seneca, in
              <title>Epistola</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e29842-Qd1e252">Nusquam est, qui ubique est.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e29842-d1e258">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e29842-Qd1e268" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e29842-Rd1e260">Seneca, in
              <title>Epistola</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e29842-Qd1e268">Vitam in peregrinatione agentibus hoc evenit, ut
              multa hospitia habeant, nullas amicitias.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
